com.sap.cloud.sdk.frameworks.liquibase

Class SchemaPerTenantProvisioner

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sap.cloud.sdk.frameworks.liquibase.SchemaPerTenantProvisioner

  • public class SchemaPerTenantProvisioner
extends Object
    This class provides helper methods with the default implementation of the tenant on-boarding and off-boarding for schema per tenant multi-tenancy. JDBC connection and a path to a liquibase configuration file for a database schema migration need to be passed during initialization.

    • Method Detail

      • subscribeTenant

        public void subscribeTenant(String tenantId)
                     throws IllegalArgumentException,
                            SQLException,
                            liquibase.exception.LiquibaseException
        This method provides the default implementation for the tenant onboarding for a given tenantId. The method creates a database schema for a tenantId based on a given connection and liquibase configuration. In this default implementation, the name of the schema is equal to tenantId.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException
        SQLException
        liquibase.exception.LiquibaseException

      • unsubscribeTenant

        public void unsubscribeTenant(String tenantId)
                       throws IllegalArgumentException,
                              SQLException
        This method provides the default implementation for the tenant offboarding for a given tenantId. It removes a corresponding database schema and all related tables.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException
        SQLException
